JOHANNESBURG - Companies listed on the Johannesburg Stock Exchange are now required to publish a compliance report on their broad-based black economic empowerment status. The JSE says the empowerment disclosure forms part of its listings requirements.READ: MTN Zakhele lists on JSE's BEE segmentCompanies need to submit this report to the JSE and to announce via the stock exchange news service that such a report is available on their website.In terms of the triple BEE regulations the report must include the entity's scores for ownership management control skills development and enterprise and supplier development.eNCA